 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT PROPOSAL: Meta-Test for Verification Pipeline — spec-to-test bilateral check. PROBLEM: 2,095 #[test] annotations across 72 files, but 233 are in guidance.rs alone. 265 invariants lack L2+ witness. No automated check verifies that each INV-* in the spec has at least one test asserting its falsification condition. The verification pipeline itself is unverified. SOLUTION: Implement a meta-test (bilateral check on the verification pipeline): for each INV-{NAMESPACE}-{NNN} in the spec, grep test files for references to that INV ID. Report unmatched INVs as verification gaps. Can be a standalone script or integrated into braid status as a verification_coverage metric. FIRST-PRINCIPLES JUSTIFICATION: C6 (falsifiability) requires every invariant to have a falsification condition. But having a falsification condition in spec text without a corresponding test is an untestable falsification condition — violating the spirit of C6. The meta-test closes the spec→test loop, making the verification pipeline itself subject to bilateral verification. This is the self-referential closure that C7 (self-bootstrap) demands: the system's verification of itself should be verifiable. VERIFICATION APPROACH: (1) Run meta-test on current codebase. (2) Expect ~265 unmatched INVs (known gap). (3) After verification sprint, expect < 50 unmatched. (4) Integrate into CI — fail if unmatched count increases. DEPENDENCIES: Independent, can be done immediately. Provides targeting data for the verification sprint (Priority 2). INTERACTS WITH: Verification sprint (provides the hit list), F(S) stagnation (explains V and I component suppression), bilateral engine (this IS a bilateral check on the test infrastructure). TRACES TO: C6 (falsifiability), C7 (self-bootstrap), INV-BILATERAL-001."
